  "text": "BT is multiple species disease to the OIE, World Organisation for Animal Health (OIE, 2009; [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and to veterinary authorities in many countries [CITATION_3] . BTV is almost exclusively spread by Culicoides spp. biting midges (Diptera) and occurs worldwide. All the serotypes can cause bluetongue disease (BT), a non-contagious hemorrhagic disease of domestic and wild ruminants and camelids with no known zoonotic potential [CITATION_4] .",
